Currently, if a new installation of JIRA is being directed to a database that already have data inside, it would throw such warning in the logs:
{code}ERROR: You have specified a database that is not empty, please specify an empty database.{code}
A similar warning will appears as well when it is being directed to a database that already have JIRA Data but in different version.

But, currently there will be no such warning when an existing JIRA instance is being directed to another JIRA instance database. JIRA would start up and continue to initialize until it is actually usable, which would led to a problem later as there is two instance using the same database. Hence, it would great if JIRA will give out warning or simply does not startup when it is being directed to another instance database.

